{
  "texts": [
    "A key challenge is the communication and cooperation between large language model and software verifier.",
    "Currently, we have implemented a top-down approach for invariant generation, i.e., we start by querying the language model for invariant candidates, validate them and then provide them to a verifier.",
    "The LLM has no knowledge about the specifics of the underlying validator or the verifier used in the process.",
    "This can ultimately hinder the large language model from generating valid (as validated by the validator) or useful (as determined by the verifier) loop invariants.",
    "During our evaluation, we already have encountered an example where this knowledge gap leads to meaningful but not validated invariant candidates (see Figure 2)."
  ]
}